man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">The winner of The Broad Prize, to be anno=
unced on Tuesday, Sept. 20 in Washington, D.C., will receive $550,000 in co=
llege scholarships for high school seniors who will graduate in 2012. The t=
hree finalist districts will each receive $150,000 in college scholarships,=
 for a total distribution of $1 million in Broad Prize scholarships.<span>&=
nbsp; </span></span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">"As we celebrate our tenth year of The Br=
oad Prize, it is significant that all four finalists this year have been fi=
nalists before," said Eli Broad, founder of The Eli and Edythe Broad Founda=
tion.<span>&nbsp; </span>"One of the most difficult challenges in public ed=
ucation is sustaining progress, but these districts have demonstrated that =
their steady focus on student achievement has indeed resulted in continued =
academic gains."</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">The finalists were selected by a </span><=
a style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; color: rgb(128, 0, 128);=
 font-size: 11.5pt;" href=3D"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=3Dheowprcab&et=
=3D1105057281224&s=3D8585&e=3D001YW2Ks2yb-6-xY-qezw27qUTXIWdkQ8L_ep1_o3zQxJ=
tVTeJrKf2f8vb612CA3-nODSEwzsW3YaQFhcm_MVAplo-5DtEpXBbl5cDJf8qkEj9lUrGtsHWYM=
TbP0YqfEjvrM4FD16hw7s5Oxah6fIpMpb3oDDczy2bTz1EznrhklSs=3D" shape=3D"rect" t=
arget=3D"_blank">review board</a><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Rom=
an','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;"> of 21 prominent education researchers, po=
licy leaders, practitioners and executives from leading universities, natio=
nal education associations, think-tanks and foundations.<span>&nbsp; </span=
>The Broad Foundation does not play a role in selecting the finalists or th=
e winner.</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-size: 11.5pt;">In the=
 2011 Broad Prize finalist districts, </span><span style=3D"font-size: 11.5=
pt;">the percent of African-American and Hispanic students in these distric=
ts performing at the highest achievement levels on state reading and math a=
ssessments were among the top third of all districts in their respective st=
ates.&nbsp; These districts also made progress in closing academic achievem=
ent gaps between minority students and their white peers at the state level=
, as well as between low-income students and their non-low-income peers at =
the state level.<span>&nbsp; </span>Additionally, in all four finalist dist=
ricts, Hispanic student participation rates increased on Advanced Placement=
 exams.</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;=
</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">All four 2011 Broad Prize finalists have =
previously been finalists.<span>&nbsp; </span>Ysleta was a finalist last ye=
ar, and Charlotte-Mecklenburg was a finalist in 2010 and in 2004.<span>&nbs=
p; </span>Miami-Dade County returns as a finalist for the fourth year, afte=
r being a finalist in 2006, 2007 and 2008.<span>&nbsp; </span>Broward retur=
ns as a three-time finalist, previously recognized in 2008 and 2009. </span=
></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">Previous Broad Prize winners have been Gw=
innett County Public Schools outside Atlanta (2010); the Aldine Independent=
 School District near Houston (2009); the Brownsville Independent School Di=
strict in Texas (2008); the New York City Department of Education (2007); B=
oston Public Schools (2006); Norfolk Public Schools in Virginia (2005); the=
 Garden Grove Unified School District in California (2004); the Long Beach =
Unified School District in California (2003); and the Houston Independent S=
chool District (2002).</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">Given changes in urban and suburban demog=
raphics over the last decade, The Broad Foundation narrowed the eligibility=
 and selection requirements for The Broad Prize this year to ensure a compa=
rison of large urban school districts.<span>&nbsp; </span>As a result, 75 l=
arge urban school districts were automatically eligible and considered for =
The Broad Prize.<span>&nbsp; </span>School districts cannot apply or be nom=
inated. In selecting the four finalists, the review board evaluated publicl=
y available academic performance data on each district that were compiled a=
nd analyzed by </span><a style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; c=
olor: rgb(128, 0, 128); font-size: 11.5pt;" href=3D"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.j=
sp?llr=3Dheowprcab&et=3D1105057281224&s=3D8585&e=3D001YW2Ks2yb-69EAfbNq84Po=
qpeM4_wGMnMOqQtqLG6D1dV0HL6UgdYZIoQXiRVyMUndCQT2W_mS31nUsMRl_cCTtEwXa9FFcp6=
7MeaHzkge_T5VTOlhEJGdg=3D=3D" shape=3D"rect" target=3D"_blank">MPR Associat=
es, Inc.</a><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; font-siz=
e: 11.5pt;">, a leading national education research consulting firm.<span>&=
nbsp; </span>The review board chose four districts that stood out in areas =
including:<i>&nbsp; &nbsp;</i></span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;"><i>&nbsp;</i></span></p>
<ul><li style=3D"margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; fo=
nt-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">Academic performa=
nce and improvement on state exams compared both with other districts in th=
e state with similar low-income student populations and with all other scho=
ol districts regardless of income levels served</li><li style=3D"margin-top=
: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman=
','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">Narrowing income and ethnic achievement gaps=
 </li><li style=3D"margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; =
font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">Improving colle=
ge readiness, as evidenced by graduation rates, SAT and ACT exam scores and=
 participation rates, and Advanced Placement exam participation and passing=
 rates<span>&nbsp; </span></li></ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">Over the next two months, teams of educat=
ional researchers and practitioners led by the education consulting company=
 </span><a style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; color: rgb(128,=
 0, 128); font-size: 11.5pt;" href=3D"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=3Dheowp=
rcab&et=3D1105057281224&s=3D8585&e=3D001YW2Ks2yb-6_sciGbK6DFRimXPBaJzJmeBj5=
6H07veHMMXRS68RqwPDOtbyjIZAsUg6BmgFt_7CHJ4h0dXGqZExmhDxXNfk-mia7EF76E37P8Fa=
qdT8ulQtWIBxfRB4KqXZyClFcnFrM=3D" shape=3D"rect" target=3D"_blank">RMC Rese=
arch Corporation</a><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; =
font-size: 11.5pt;"> will conduct site visits in each finalist district to =
gather qualitative information, interview district administrators, conduct =
focus groups with teachers and principals and observe classrooms. The teams=
 will also interview parents, community leaders, school board members and u=
nion representatives. A </span><a style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Roman','=
serif'; color: rgb(128, 0, 128); font-size: 11.5pt;" href=3D"http://r20.rs6=
.net/tn.jsp?llr=3Dheowprcab&et=3D1105057281224&s=3D8585&e=3D001YW2Ks2yb-6-o=
LitMvzrYon_W92T2HKlJPl9czZ0hic2bmE4zrXwhf507qOBEMqtbnTkCRzX6xc-lxoG-qZXnR8d=
wL1ZLdZuC-WNDOLh3eyWVTsbzg4F0Ug0iWwlEGSsJT47mMIPI_cT_zrMYnOLHRcEOVFYzDrcF3g=
9IYX4lapM=3D" shape=3D"rect" target=3D"_blank">selection jury</a><span styl=
e=3D"font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;"> of promin=
ent individuals from business, industry, education and public service will =
then review all resulting quantitative and qualitative data to choose the w=
inning school district.</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">For more information about The Broad Priz=
e, this year's finalists, the review board and selection jury, please visit=
 </span><a style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; color: rgb(128,=
 0, 128); font-size: 11.5pt;" href=3D"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=3Dheowp=
rcab&et=3D1105057281224&s=3D8585&e=3D001YW2Ks2yb-682p20eQ49gCxiOvG0RWe-jtiv=
LVDABvsm9pi11R-UcS-LDoE3FXvakdSvbnv6_npWICcuC_eWLZop51zNxyfSTxe_fM517lAd8fo=
QVb6XEgw=3D=3D" shape=3D"rect" target=3D"_blank">www.broadprize.org</a><spa=
n style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">.</s=
pan></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: 'Times New Ro=
man','serif'; font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><a style=3D"color: rgb(128, 0, 128); font=
-size: 11.5pt;" href=3D"http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?llr=3Dheowprcab&et=3D1105=
057281224&s=3D8585&e=3D001YW2Ks2yb-6-oLitMvzrYoubOw9qCc6AjJVvajIgQywRZCp02r=
e_dhftwLzGa1t6nOpMCVsV6paxeqnHxPBpqwk0Ho3KhtYNDw6293oZ98b63m8zFBd3YXkn056Ub=
6o9I" shape=3D"rect" target=3D"_blank">The Eli and Edythe Broad Foundation<=
/a><span style=3D"font-size: 11.5pt;"> is a national venture philanthropy e=
stablished by entrepreneur Eli Broad to advance entrepreneurship for the pu=
blic good in education, science and the arts.<span>&nbsp; </span>The Broad =
Foundation's education work is focused on dramatically improving urban K-12=
 public education through better governance, management, labor relations an=
d competition. The Broad Foundation's Internet address is </span><a style=
